liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The Maroons try something out the box and kick off the first, for Hamiso Tabuai-Fidow to chase, but fortunately for the Blues it was James Tedesco who got back and slid onto the ball to end an absorbing half of Origin football.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Half time: Queensland 10-6 New South Wales

children.content: The Maroons try something out the box and kick off the first, for Hamiso Tabuai-Fidow to chase, but fortunately for the Blues it was James Tedesco who got back and slid onto the ball to end an absorbing half of Origin football.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Brilliant line from Liam Martin! He came through untouched through a huge gap on the left edge between Cherry Evans and Val Holmes. Cleary and Luai with the passes to set it up as the Panthers combine to put the Blues on the board. Kick is good, Queensland's lead is cut to 10-6. GAME ON!
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 32' TRY NEW SOUTH WALES!

children.content: He came through untouched through a huge gap on the left edge between Cherry Evans and Val Holmes.
Cleary and Luai with the passes to set it up as the Panthers combine to put the Blues on the board.
Kick is good, Queensland's lead is cut to 10-6.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Tom Gilbert won't return. He has a dislocated shoulder. Does that mean Reuben Cotter won't get a breather this match? That could be huge later on.
